  "prompt": "How hot does Austin, TX get?",
  "response": "Austin, Texas, is known for its hot summers, which can be quite intense. On average, summer temperatures in Austin typically range from the mid-90s to the low 100s Fahrenheit (35-38\u00b0C). However, during heatwaves, temperatures can soar even higher, sometimes exceeding 105\u00b0F (40.5\u00b0C).\n\nThe hottest months are usually July and August, where daytime highs often stay above 100\u00b0F (37.8\u00b0C). Nighttime temperatures during these months usually drop into the mid-70s to low 80s Fahrenheit (24-28\u00b0C), offering some relief.\n\nHumidity levels can vary, but Austin often experiences a mix of dry and humid conditions, which can make the heat feel even more oppressive. Heat indices, which factor in humidity, can make it feel like it's in the 100s\u00b0F (37.8\u00b0C) or higher.\n\nIt's important to stay hydrated, wear sun protection, and limit outdoor activities during peak heat hours when visiting or living in Austin during the summer months.",
